post_text:
College Credit plus Parent Info Night will be held on October 3rd, 2019, Thursday 5 PM. Please check in at the front office for the location of the presentation.

College Credit Plus

Ohio‚Äôs new College Credit Plus can help you earn college and high school credits at the same time by taking college courses from colleges and/or universities. The purpose of this program is to promote rigorous academic pursuits and to provide a wide variety of options to college-ready students. Taking a College Credit Plus course from a public college or university is free, which means no cost for tuition, books, or fees. If you choose to attend a private college or university, you may have limited costs. Your high school may have an agreement with a local college for specific courses; however, you can choose to take College Credit Plus courses that would benefit your future from any college. This includes online courses.

post_text:
Noble Academy is looking for a qualified candidate to oversee our before and after school enrichment program for the 2019-2020 school year. The program is in it‚Äôs first year and based on the 21st Century Community Learning Centers Grant. The hours would be Monday-Thursday 1pm-7pm and Saturday 9am-1pm. The program will offer academic enrichment to selected students as well as other activities that focus on youth development, social emotional learning, civic engagement and nutritional and physical health.

Applicant responsibilities will include, but may not be limited to: attending training meetings, setting up student programs, student attendance, communication with parents and community outreach. Qualified applicants should be comfortable with Microsoft Excel. Position is contingent on Noble Academy receiving the 21st Century Grant. If interested please send your resume to info@noblecolumbus.org.

post_text:
It is with great sadness that we are posting this fundraiser for the family of one of our students, Justina Benge. Justina passed away last Friday. She has been part of our Concept family since 2010. Our hope is to raise money to help cover the funeral costs for this family as we grieve the loss of this sweet girl.
Please consider donating at the following link:
https://www.gofundme.com/JustinaBenge
